      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "5b64d9fb0d5c5f292548c23e7841cc30f7a8423e",
            "subject": "LU-10703 nodemap: save and clear fileset correctly"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Wang Shilong",
          "email": "wshilong@ddn.com",
          "date": "2018-03-22 05:59:55.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2018-04-09 19:45:09.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-10837 ldiskfs: skip bitmap check if block bitmap is uninitialized",
        "message": "LU-10837 ldiskfs: skip bitmap check if block bitmap is uninitialized\n\nSee comments in ext4_free_clusters_after_init:\n/* Return the number of free blocks in a block group.  It is used when\n * the block bitmap is uninitialized, so we can't just count the bits\n * in the bitmap. */\nSo extra check we enhanced here is wrong if this block group\nbitmap is uninitialized, since we only check bitmaps here.\n\nFurther, Looking at EXT4_BG_BLOCK_UNINIT clear codes, Kernel\nwill reinit free_clusters_count when tried to clear the flag, so\nextra check for uninited block bitmaps dosen't make much sense.\n\nLet's skip uninited block bitmap check if EXT4_BG_BLOCK_UNINIT\nis set, whatever free count group desc recorded is untrustable somehow\n\nChange-Id: I845f2e0e17e53b7e3073399bd8b0a85e3db66ef8\nSigned-off-by: Wang Shilong <wshilong@ddn.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/31720\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
  "requirements": [],
  "submit_records": []
}